<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Oracle Adapter insert function  adds quote to tablename and causes the query to throw (table/view not found) exception.</p>

<p>I am using Oracle Database Express Edition.</p>

<p>The following is the php statement in zend framework</p>

<pre><code>    // build the statement
    $sql = "INSERT INTO "
         . $this-&gt;quoteIdentifier($table, true)
         . ' (' . implode(', ', $cols) . ') '
         . 'VALUES (' . implode(', ', $vals) . ')';
</code></pre>

<p>The function starts working once you change the above  line to replacing  $this-&gt;quoteIdentifier($table, true)  with $table:</p>

<pre><code>    // build the statement
    $sql = "INSERT INTO "
         . $table 
         . ' (' . implode(', ', $cols) . ') '
         . 'VALUES (' . implode(', ', $vals) . ')';
</code></pre>

